{{Quote|He did it again; Representative Jar Jar Binks (Naboo) accidentally destroyed an elaborate ice statue at a gala fundraiser in Coruscant's posh Jrade-district last night.|A HoloNet News report detailing Binks' accident in Jrade Plaza|<ref name="HoloNet" />}}
'''Jrade Plaza''' was located in the [[Jrade District/Legends|Jrade District]] in [[Galactic City/Legends|Galactic City]] on<ref name="HoloNet" /> the [[Planet/Legends|planet]]<ref name="TEA">''[[The Essential Atlas]]''</ref> [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]].<ref name="HoloNet" /> It was capable of holding thousands of spectators<ref name="Memorial">{{InsiderCite|73|Republic HoloNet News Core Edition 15:01:13}}</ref> and, during the [[Time/Legends|time]] of the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]], contained the [[Chancellery Walkway]], which was lined with monuments and memorials to the most influential [[Supreme Chancellor/Legends|Supreme Chancellors]].<ref name="Encyclopedia">{{CSWECite|I|119|Chancellery Walkway}}</ref>

In [[23 BBY/Legends|23 BBY]],<ref name="Date1">[[HoloNet News Vol. 531|''HoloNet News Vol. 531 #45'']] takes place on [[Great ReSynchronization|13:2:28]], which corresponds to [[23 BBY/Legends|23 BBY]] per the reasoning [[Template:YearMathGRS|here]].</ref> an exclusive gala<ref name="Fact">{{FactFile|54|JAR 9-10|Jar Jar Binks}}</ref> fundraiser was held in Jrade Plaza, where [[Junior Representative/Legends|Representative]] [[Jar Jar Binks/Legends|Jar Jar Binks]] tucked a tablecloth into his cummerbund,<ref name="HoloNet" /> as he had observed [[Senator/Legends|Senator]] [[Orn Free Taa/Legends|Orn Free Taa]] do so on numerous occasions. Binks' exaggerated conversational gestures led him to knock a tray of [[Canapé/Legends|canapés]] out of a waiter's [[Limb/Legends|hands]]. When the representative dived for them, he accidentally pulled the tablecloth and destroyed a priceless<ref name="Fact" /> and intricate<ref name="HoloNet" /> [[Water/Legends|ice]] statue crafted by [[Artist/Legends|sculptor]] [[Kime Enanrum]], leading the plaza to appear as though it had been snowing for [[Standard hour/Legends|hours]] afterwards.<ref name="Fact" /> The incident was reported the following [[Standard day/Legends|day]] in the [[Great ReSynchronization|13:2:28]] issue of the [[HoloNet News CoCo District Edition]].<ref name="HoloNet" />

==Behind the scenes==
{{Quote|Though a memorial to Finis Valorum had been approved and planned for the Jrade Plaza Chancellery Walkway immediately following his death in the terrorist attack of 14:9:19, the plaza's public shutdown for security investigations delayed the unveiling for weeks.|A HoloNet News report describing the Finis Valorum Memorial in Jrade Plaza|<ref name="Memorial" />}}
Jrade Plaza was first mentioned in [[HoloNet News Vol. 531|''HoloNet News Vol. 531 #45'']], an [[in-universe]] issue of the [[HoloNet News/Legends|HoloNet News]]<ref name="HoloNet" /> written by [[Pablo Hidalgo]] and [[Paul Ens]]<ref name="Credits">{{HoloNetNewsWeb||credits.html|Credits}}</ref> and published on the [[HoloNet News (original website)|HoloNet News]] website in [[2002]].<ref name="HoloNet" />

[[File:ValorumPortrait-SWE.png|thumb|right|250px|A memorial for Finis Valorum was placed inside Jrade Plaza, which had its canonicity status affected by later sources.]]
The plaza was later mentioned in "[[Republic HoloNet News Core Edition 15:01:13]]," an in-universe news report also written by Hidalgo and published in the [[Star Wars Insider 73|seventy-third issue]] of the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine<ref name="Memorial" /> on [[December 26]], [[2003]].<ref name="SW.com">{{SWArchive|url=community/news/2003/12/news20031219.html|text=Mark Hamill On Stage In ''Insider'' #73}}</ref> The report covers the unveiling of a [[Finis Valorum Memorial|memorial]] for the recently [[Death/Legends|deceased]] former Supreme Chancellor [[Finis Valorum/Legends|Finis Valorum]]<ref name="Memorial" /> in [[21 BBY/Legends|21 BBY]].<ref name="Date2">{{InsiderCite|73|Republic HoloNet News Core Edition 15:01:13}} places the unveiling of the [[Finis Valorum Memorial]] on [[Great ReSynchronization|15:01:13]], which corresponds to [[21 BBY/Legends|21 BBY]] per the reasoning [[Template:YearMathGRS|here]].</ref> Valorum was later shown to still be alive<ref name="The Lost One">{{TCW|The Lost One}}</ref> by [[20 BBY/Legends|20 BBY]]<ref name="Fact File">{{FactFile2014|60|20 BBY 67-70|Sifo-Dyas' Legacy}} places the events of "[[The Lost One]]" in [[20 BBY/Legends|20 BBY]].</ref> in "[[The Lost One]]," an episode of the [[The Clone Wars: The Lost Missions|sixth season]] of ''[[Star Wars: The Clone Wars]]''<ref name="The Lost One" /> that first aired on [[March 1]], [[2014]].<ref name="Air date">{{WebCite|url=https://www.fernsehserien.de/star-wars-the-clone-wars/episodenguide/staffel-6/9660|text=Star Wars: The Clone Wars Staffel 6 Episodenguide|work=[https://www.fernsehserien.de www.fernsehserien.de]|archivedate=20190419012747}}</ref> rendering the [[canon]]icity of his death according to the HoloNet News article<ref name="Date2" /> within the [[Star Wars Legends|''Star Wars'' Legends]] continuity<ref name="Legends">{{SW|url=news/the-legendary-star-wars-expanded-universe-turns-a-new-page|text=The Legendary Star Wars Expanded Universe Turns a New Page}}</ref> uncertain.

In the report, the Finis Valorum Memorial was approved and planned for the Chancellery Walkway in Jrade Plaza following Valorum's death in the [[terrorist attack of 14:9:19]]. The plaza was shut down to the public for several [[Standard week/Legends|weeks]] over security concerns, which delayed the unveiling. The memorial eventually opened to a small crowd of 200 spectators, which was reported on in the [[HoloNet News Core Edition]].<ref name="Memorial" />

